race.comment: A good field has been assembled for the inaugural Golden Saddle and MAGNIFICENT ANDY (1) is top of the pops from what we have seen recently. He went into The Quokka first-up and was only 1L off Jokers Grin there. Trials coming in have been good by his standard and with a favourable gate, he can land the knockout blow. HANCHI (6) may be over the odds following a big return to form 35 days ago at Belmont. He was forced to trial by the Stipes following that effort and he was very impressive there. Up to 1200m is no issue, he draws well and he should get his chance. Stablemate TWAIN'S ANGEL (10) comes through the same trial where she got the job one in good fashion. She was too good in The Joey to end last campaign and she tends to fire first-up. Rates highly and can feature. SNOWDOME (4) impressed in a recent trial and can make his presence felt. YONGA LASS (11) has the class to sprint well fresh as she did in The Joey first-up last campaign.
